# Keep the Vercel deployment lean and under the function size limit. The runtime needs
# only: app/ (traced from the import), the innetwork* static assets + the payers/*.roaring
# membership bitmaps (both pulled in via vercel.json includeFiles), and requirements.txt.

# The local SQLite files hold only ephemeral caches now; the function creates a fresh one
# in /tmp. Verified insurance is served from the read-only payers/ bitmaps (mmap'd), so
# the old gzipped SQLite seed is no longer shipped or inflated.
innetwork.db
innetwork.db-wal
innetwork.db-shm
innetwork.db.gz

# Node/JS toolchain — the frontend bundle (innetwork.bundle.js) is prebuilt + committed,
# so Vercel must NOT see package.json (it would detect a Node project, run npm, and expect
# a static output directory — and fail). Keep innetwork.config.js: it's served at runtime.
package.json
package-lock.json
build.mjs
eslint.config.js
vitest.config.js
playwright.config.js
jsconfig.json
.prettierrc
.prettierignore

# pyproject.toml here is tool config only (ruff/mypy/pytest) — it has NO [project] table,
# so Vercel's uv-based Python builder errors trying to install from it. Hide it so the
# builder falls back to the pinned requirements.txt. Nothing reads it at runtime.
pyproject.toml

# Dev-only / not needed at serve time.
.venv/
__pycache__/
node_modules/
tests/
tests-e2e/
src/
docs/
deploy/
loadtest/
sample_medicare.csv
*.bat
.github/
.git/
